l exchanges and study tours  Institute Honors Established for students who achieve at high levels  the program includes honors courses  with enrollment limited to 12  special forums on current events  and a capstone senior honors project or thesis  Graduating with Institute Honors is the highest academic achievement at VMI  These cadets may also be recognized via national awards such as the Rhodes  Marshall  and Gates scholarships  VMI has had 11 Rhodes scholars to date  Service Learning The VMI experience emphasizes the value of service by preparing cadets to become citizen soldiers who will serve their country and communities  To that end  VMI s Community Outreach and Renewal Experience   the CORE initiative  offers opportunities to learn about service at the local  national  and international levels  Classroom experiences and hands on participation in community projects give cadets an awareness of the importance of service in the lives of citizen soldiers  Rhodes Scholars VMI has educated 11 Rhodes scholars since 1921  Chosen for outstanding scholarly achievements  character  commitment to others and to the common good  and their potential for leadership  a successful applicant must excel in both academic and athletic pursuits  Are you the next Rhodes scholar  Gregory E  Lippiatt Michael N  Lokale Robert C  Randolph Josiah Bunting III Lee Douglas Badgett George Washington Hardy III William Bridwell Adams Robert Marston John W  Pendleton Henry Harrison Cooke Samuel Walter Washington I am very proud to leave the Leadership Book Club as my legacy  At VMI I discovered I was capable of more than I had thought  Trevor Tafolla   14 Co Founder  Leadership Book Club Hometown  Richmond  Virginia Major  Civil Engineering Trevor s Day in the Life Viewbook Links College Fairs FAQs Financial Aid Tuition   Fees Schedule VMI s Institutional Profile Follow  Then lead  Resources VMI CEEB Code  005858 Financial Aid FAFSA Code  003753 Students and their families are encouraged to us